snippet.title: Anime “Dragon Ball Super: Beerus” | SUPER Launch Trailer
snippet.description:
Series Premieres in Fall of 2026!
The anime Dragon Ball Super, original work, story, and character design by Akira Toriyama, is set to begin anew as Dragon Ball Super: Beerus in Fall 2026!

#dragonball #dragonballsuper

◾️INTRODUCTION
The globally beloved manga DRAGON BALL by Akira Toriyama continues to captivate fans through a wide range of media—from TV animation, movies, games, and merchandising—standing as a top-ranked title with extraordinary worldwide popularity. 
Now, in 2026, the anime Dragon Ball Super, original work, story, and character design by Akira Toriyama, is set to begin anew as Dragon Ball Super: Beerus! This ENHANCED edition introduces a large volume of newly added and redrawn cuts, as well as a reconstructed narrative. With cutting-edge visual expression, the series delivers even more immersive battle scenes and a more faithful representation of the original manga—bringing an ENHANCED edition to life like never before.

Several years have passed since the fierce battle against Majin Buu, and Earth has finally regained a brief moment of peace. At the same time, Beerus, the God of Destruction, awakens from his long, deep sleep. Even Kai and Supreme Kai, aware of Beerus’s overwhelming power to destroy entire planets, watch his awakening with great fear… Meanwhile, Beerus hears rumors of a Saiyan who defeated Frieza—and suddenly appears before Goku.
Targeted by Beerus, the strongest being in the universe, Earth is in grave danger. Thus begins an Earth-shattering cosmic battle between the God of Destruction and Goku and his allies—a conflict that will shake the entire universe.

Original Work, Story & Character Design: Akira Toriyama

snippet.title: (2026) NEW DRAGON BALL SUPER ANIME - MORO ARC OFFICIAL TRAILER REVEAL!
snippet.description:
Big & Major News in the world of Dragon Ball Super! Dragon Ball Super Anime - Moro Arc Officially Revealed! No news on any Dragon Ball Super - Anime Remake as of the time of the Genkimakatsu event, but yes!

Current Description so far: At this event, Iyoku decided to reveal this trailer. Which shows the Galactic Patrol Arc. Specifically, Goku & Vegeta in their outfits! Remember, in the Moro arc, we saw stuff like

Perfected Ultra Instinct Goku VS Moro 73
MUI Goku VS UI/Angel Powers Moro
Mastered Ultra Instinct Goku VS Planet Moro

Moro arc also included Merus, Saganbo, Prime Moro, and a lot of interesting stuff! Hope you enjoy, as I'm excited for this new chapter!

#dragonballsuperanime
#moroarc
#muigoku 


A Dragon Ball Super Remake has officially been revealed, confirming a full re-adaptation of the Dragon Ball Super storyline that follows the manga continuity written and illustrated by Toyotarō.

This remake realigns Dragon Ball Super from the very beginning, reworking the anime to match the manga’s structure, tone, power scaling, and narrative consistency. The project begins with Battle of Gods and Resurrection ‘F’, retold with manga-accurate pacing and character development, removing many of the inconsistencies that defined the original television run.

The Dragon Ball Super Remake fully covers the major Super arcs in correct chronological order, including:
• Battle of Gods
• Resurrection ‘F’
• Universe 6 vs Universe 7 Tournament
• Goku Black and Future Trunks Arc
• Tournament of Power
• Dragon Ball Super: Broly

Timestamps:
Trailer: 0:00
Discussion: 4:58

Each arc is completely reanimated with modern production quality, improved fight choreography, cleaner animation, stronger dramatic weight, and a tighter narrative flow. Character motivations, transformations, and power progression follow the manga more closely, resulting in a more coherent and grounded Dragon Ball Super experience.

The remake also officially adapts post-Tournament of Power manga arcs for the first time in animated form. This includes the Moro Arc, featuring Moro in his fully animated debut, along with expanded lore surrounding galactic patrols, divine techniques, and large-scale planetary battles.

Additionally, the remake continues into the Granola the Survivor Arc, introducing Granola, Ultra Ego Vegeta, Black Frieza, and True Ultra Instinct Goku. These arcs push Dragon Ball Super into a darker, more strategic era, emphasizing refined techniques, consequences, and long-term character evolution rather than constant power escalation.

Ultra Instinct is redefined through its manga portrayal, highlighting Perfected Ultra Instinct and later True Ultra Instinct, while Vegeta’s path diverges with the official introduction of Ultra Ego, reinforcing his unique approach to power and combat philosophy. Black Frieza’s emergence establishes a new top-tier threat that reshapes the hierarchy of power across the Dragon Ball universe.

This video provides a complete breakdown of the Dragon Ball Super Remake reveal, including:
• Full arc list and chronological structure
• Differences between the original DBS anime and the manga-based remake
• Moro Arc animation details and narrative importance
• Granola Arc characters and transformations
• Ultra Ego Vegeta, True Ultra Instinct, and Black Frieza explained
• What this remake means for Dragon Ball’s future anime direction

The Dragon Ball Super Remake represents a definitive retelling of the Super era, correcting past inconsistencies, elevating production quality, and finally bringing the full manga storyline to animation in a cohesive, long-form format.

snippet.title: Supergirl | Blast Off :30
snippet.description:
It’s called making an entrance. #Supergirl lands in theaters and IMAX June 26.

“Supergirl,” DC Studios’ newest feature film to hit the big screen, will be in theaters worldwide this summer from Warner Bros. Pictures, starring Milly Alcock in the dual role of Supergirl/Kara Zor-El. Craig Gillespie directs the film from a screenplay by Ana Nogueira.

When an unexpected and ruthless adversary strikes too close to home, Kara Zor-El, aka Supergirl, reluctantly joins forces with an unlikely companion on an epic, interstellar journey of vengeance and justice.

Alcock stars alongside Matthias Schoenaerts, Eve Ridley, David Krumholtz, Emily Beecham, and Jason Momoa. DC Studios heads Peter Safran and James Gunn are producing the film, which is based on characters from DC, Supergirl based on characters created by Jerry Siegel and Joe Shuster.

The film is executive produced by Nigel Gostelow, Chantal Nong Vo and Lars P. Winther. Behind the camera, Gillespie is joined by director of photography Rob Hardy, production designer Neil Lamont, editor Tatiana S. Riegel, costume designer Anna B. Sheppard, Visual Effects Supervisor Geoffrey Baumann, and composer Ramin Djawadi.

DC Studios Presents a Troll Court Entertainment Production, The Safran Company Production, A Film by Craig Gillespie, “Supergirl,” which will be in theaters and IMAX® across North America on June 26, 2026, and internationally beginning 24 June 2026, distributed by Warner Bros. Pictures.

snippet.title: WWE 2K26 Attitude Era Edition: First Details & Trailer Breakdown!
snippet.description:
WWE 2K26 is set to feature the return of the Attitude Era, with a new trailer revealing the game will include a special Attitude Era edition featuring classic versions of stars from 1997-2002!

The new Attitude Era edition of WWE 2K26 was revealed during Smackdown, with WWE airing a trailer featuring the stars who appear on the cover, including:

- Stone Cold Steve Austin
- The Rock
- Kane
- The Undertaker
- Shawn Michaels
- Triple H
- Kurt Angle
- Chyna
- Trish Stratus
- Lita
- Stephanie McMahon
- The Dudley Boyz

All 13 of the Attitude Era stars are now confirmed for the WWE 2K26 roster, where it's expected we'll see younger versions of these stars included as part of a special Attitude Era Bonus DLC Pack.

Potentially offering up clues on what players can expect to see in WWE 2K26, the Attitude Era trailer teases several younger versions of stars, while also appearing to tease the return of the Inferno Match which was listed as a new match type in recent leaks.
